First Lady Michelle Obama has announced that pediatrician Judith S. Palfrey, M.D., will lead the Let's Move! childhood obesity initiative as Executive Director. Dr. Palfrey has been a pediatric clinician and teacher for over 30 years, providing clinical care to children and families, conducting pediatric research, and leading major medical organizations. She has been a long-time supporter of the Let's Move! campaign and spoke at its launch in 2010 as president of the American Academy of Pediatrics. Dr. Palfrey's appointment is aimed at continuing the efforts to combat childhood obesity and empower parents to make healthier choices for their children. She brings a wealth of clinical, research, and practice expertise to the role.